  <div class="descriptionburrito">
    <br> Wondering whats so special about <em> yayas </em> recipe? </br>
    <br> This burrito is not only delcious, healthy and easy to make, it is made with no animal products and is gluten free!
  <br> Check out more <strong> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/yayas_eatin_good/"
     itemprop="sameAs"><span itemprop="author"> @yayas_eatin_good </span>
</a> </strong> for more food inspiration&#33; </br>
  </div>

  <nav>
  <dt><a href="#ingredients"><b>Ingredients</b></a></dt>
          <dt><a href="#directions"><b>Directions</b></a></dt>
        </nav>

<ul class="text">

  <li class="col">
    <div class="ingredients" id="hccingredients">
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
      <ul itemprop="Ingredient">
        <li> &#8531; cup <b>refried beans</b></li>
          <li><b>1 large brown rice tortilla</b></li>
    <li> 1 cup <b>kale</b></li>
    <li>&#188; cup <b>red onion</b></li>
    <li>&#188; cup <b>tomatoe</b></li>
    <li>&#188; cup <b>salsa</b> of your choice (I love <b>peach salsa</b> the best!</li>
    <li>2 tbsp <b>vegan sour cream</b> or <b>vegan cream cheese</b></li>
    <li>Tofu scramble which requires:</li> <li> 1 serving <b>firm tofu</b>, 2 tbsp <b>nutritional yeast</b>, 1 teaspoon <b>cumin</b>, 1 tsp <b>cumin</b>, 1 tsp <b>tumeric</b> and 1 tbsp <b>garlic salt</b>.</li>
  </ul>
    </div>
  </li>


  <li class="col">
    <div class="directions" id="hccdirections">
    <h2>Directions</h2>
    <ol itemprop="recipeInstructions">
      <li><p>First preheat oven to <b>350</b> then heat a <i>non-stick pan</i> over <b>medium heat</b>.</p></li>
      <li><p>Spread refried beans onto torilla and put in oven.</p></li>
      <figure>
           <img itemprop="image" src="https://eatrunwritelove.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/img_4882.jpg" alt="1 Pic">
        </figure> </li>
<li><p>Break tofu into quarter size crumbles in <i>bowl</i> and add seasonings. Mix well before dumping in hot pan.</p></li>
      <li><p>Chop up red onion, tomatoe and kale into bite-size pieces, while occasionally stiring tofu in pan.</p></li>
           <img itemprop="image" src="http://couponclippingcook.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/12-cut-tomatoes.jpg" alt="2 Pic">
         </figure>
      </li>
      <li><p>Add veggies to pan and stir for <time datetime="5m"><b>4-5 minutes</b></time>, or until hot.</p></li>
            <li><p>Take out warmed tortilla from oven, and top with tofu and veggie mixture from the pan.</p></li>
            <li><p>Top with salsa and sour cream.</p></li>
            <li><p> Don't forget to <em>enjoy</em> and keep <em>eatin goood</em> </li>
      <figure>
            <img itemprop="image" src="https://img.clipartfest.com/c805a07e96fbdd6bfb0aed19b310f6f1_e7a6d541474ab8ea909a7391e96f11-pink-heart-clipart-no-background_360-288.png" alt="3 Pic">
          </figure>
      </li>

  </div>
</ul>

